  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Actor
    An Actor represents anything in Mater Tua that can move.
    Enemy
    An Enemy represents anything in Mater Tua that can deal damage to the Player, and that the Player must kill to advance.
    EnemyStrong
    An EnemyStrong is a special type of enemy that has more health and does more damage than the typical enemy.
    Goal
    A Goal represents anything in Mater Tua that the player must touch to move on to the next level.
    InstructionScreen
    The InstructionScreen displays Mater Tua's instructions.
    Level
    A Level object takes in a txt file of a level and translates it into an ArrayList with Solid objects.
    Main
    The Main class runs the program.
    Obstacle
    An Obstacle represents anything in Mater Tua that Actors cannot move through, and are unable to move.
    Overworld
    The Overworld handles all graphics, user-game interactions, and level progression.
    Player
    A Player represents the entity that the person playing Mater Tua controls.
    Projectile
    A Proejctile<\code> represents anything in Mater Tua that is fired by Actors towards other Actors, and deals damage to Actors on contact.
    SFileIO
    The SFileIO class handles creating objects from files and converting an object into a file.
    Tester1  
    TitleScreen
    The TitleScreen is the screen the user sees upon opening the game.
